t4431.text: Of course whatever the analysis shows, in practice we are a long way off a rate of mitigation that would avoid the need for big C-. And hard sectors remain hard. We need to work on CCUS! But maybe be cautious about IAM results anyway.

t4432.text: IPCC WGIII has heard criticism and asked modelers to use much lower discount rates in AR6 work. Will be interesting to see if this affects the amount of C- in the scenarios!

t4433.text: High abatement cost estimates plus significant discount rates, in a scenario constrained to produce a 1.5C-compatible pathway, may increase reliance on novel and expensive C- tech: future costs get discounted, so best path looks like doing less mitigation now and more C- later.

t4434.text: IAMs scenarios assessed in IPCC SR1.5 mostly relied on substantial C- to bolster emissions cuts. But IAMs have a *lot* of problems, including overestimating abatement costs and high discount rates (+ less relevant in this case, underpricing climate impacts).
